The best way to remember phrasal verbs is to make learning fun and interactive. Here are a few effective strategies to keep them in mind:

Use Them in Daily Conversation: Try to incorporate phrasal verbs in your conversations or writing. For example, when talking about your day, say things like, "I need to press on with my tasks."在日常對話中使用它們：嘗試在對話或寫作中加入短語動詞。例如，在談論你的一天時，可以說「我需要繼續完成我的任務」。

Create Flashcards: Write the phrasal verb on one side and its meaning and example on the other. Reviewing these flashcards regularly can help with memorization.建立抽認卡：一邊寫下片語動詞，另一邊寫下其意義和範例。定期複習這些抽認卡可以幫助記憶。

Group by Theme: Learn phrasal verbs that are related to the same topic, such as travel (e.g., get out, set off) or work (e.g., press on, point out). Grouping them by theme can make them easier to remember.按主題分組：學習與相同主題相關的片語動詞，例如旅行（例如， get out 、 set off ）或工作（例如， press on 、 point out ）。按主題對它們進行分組可以使它們更容易記住。

Visualize Scenarios: Picture situations where you’d use the phrasal verb. If you visualize yourself in a rainstorm saying, “Let’s get out of here,” you’ll remember it better.視覺化場景：想像您將使用片語動詞的情況。如果你想像自己在暴風雨中說：“我們離開這裡吧”，你會記得更清楚。

Practice with Stories: Write short stories or sentences using multiple phrasal verbs. This will help reinforce their meaning and usage in context.故事練習：使用多個片語動詞寫短故事或句子。這將有助於強化它們在上下文中的含義和用法。

Play Language Games: Use apps or websites that have language games specifically for phrasal verbs. It makes practice more enjoyable and effective.玩語言遊戲：使用專門針對短語動詞的語言遊戲的應用程式或網站。它使練習變得更加愉快和有效。